Installation Guide for Windows
NOTICE: Ensure file names and directories are exact for successful build/compilation.

Prerequisites
Use PowerShell or similar terminal (avoid Command Prompt)

Setup
Enter into Terminal

Create and navigate to the build directory: 

> mkdir C:\Users\[YOUR_USERNAME]\dev\zen.script\
> cd C:\Users\[YOUR_USERNAME]\dev\zen.script\

Note: Remain in this directory for all subsequent steps.

Download required files from GitHub:
https://github.com/kittykatkode/zen.script/blob/main/zen_script.py
https://github.com/kittykatkode/zen.script/tree/main/assets/logos

Installation & Building
Run these commands in order:

# Install dependencies
> pip install pyinstaller
> pyinstaller --version  # Verify installation
> pip install pillow
> python.exe -m pip install --upgrade pip

# Build the application
> python zen_script.py
> pyinstaller --onefile --windowed --name zen.script zen_script.py
> pyinstaller --onefile --windowed --icon=logo_zen_dot.ico zen_script.py


Your finished application will be located at:
C:\Users\[YOUR_USERNAME]\dev\zen.script\dist\zen_script.exe

Note: zen_script runs locally directly from the \dev\ directory.
